mvector LOCAL mvector

NAME

mjo_vector_type — get the string representation of a variant

SYNOPSIS

#include <mvector.h>

void
unsigned char const*(enum mjo_vector_variant const i_type);

DESCRIPTION

Get the string representation of a variant.

Following is a description of the arguments.

i_type
a value from the ‘enum mjo_vector_variant’ list

RETURN VALUE

If i_type is invalid, an empty string is returned.

A string representing the data type of a variant.
